            <div class="help-section">
                <h3>Basic Gameplay</h3>
                <p>This is a Texas Hold'em Poker game. Each player is dealt two private cards (hole cards). Five community cards are dealt face-up on the 'board'. Players use their hole cards along with the community cards to make the best possible five-card poker hand.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="help-section">
                <h3>Betting Rounds</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Pre-flop:</strong> After hole cards are dealt.</li>
                    <li><strong>Flop:</strong> After the first three community cards are dealt.</li>
                    <li><strong>Turn:</strong> After the fourth community card is dealt.</li>
                    <li><strong>River:</strong> After the fifth community card is dealt.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>In each round, players can Check, Bet, Call, Raise, or Fold.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="help-section">
                <h3>Hand Rankings (Highest to Lowest)</h3>
                <div class="hand-ranking"><span class="hand-ranking-name">Royal Flush</span> <span class="hand-ranking-example">A K Q J 10 (same suit)</span></div>
                <div class="hand-ranking"><span class="hand-ranking-name">Straight Flush</span> <span class="hand-ranking-example">8 7 6 5 4 (same suit)</span></div>
                <div class="hand-ranking"><span class="hand-ranking-name">Four of a Kind</span> <span class="hand-ranking-example">A A A A K</span></div>
                <div class="hand-ranking"><span class="hand-ranking-name">Full House</span> <span class="hand-ranking-example">K K K Q Q</span></div>
                <div class="hand-ranking"><span class="hand-ranking-name">Flush</span> <span class="hand-ranking-example">A K J 9 2 (all same suit)</span></div>
